    <section id="import-auto-idm228637152">
      <title>Questions with be  </title>
      <section id="import-auto-idm424038080">
        <title>We can ask for information by using the verb to be. </title>
        <para id="import-auto-idm210549952">.</para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm508799680">Are you a plumber? Yes, I’m a plumber. </para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm264404096">Is he a carpenter? No, he’s a plumber.</para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm508150128">Is she an architect? Yes, she’s an architect.</para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm512898672">Are you bricklayers? No we’re carpenters.</para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm269689424">Are they electricians? Yes, they’re electricians.</para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm269059312">.</para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm475477904">Note how we shorten some of the words: she is (she’s), we are (we’re) and they are (they’re).</para>
      </section>
