      <section id="import-auto-idm428523072">
        <title>Read the text and discuss the questions.</title>
        <para id="import-auto-idm446619296">The Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) is a political and economic organization made up of ten Southeast Asian countries. The organization was formed on 8 August 1967 by the countries of Indonesia, the Philippines, Singapore, Malaysia and Thailand. Brunei, Burma (Myanmar), Cambodia, Laos, and Vietnam have also joined the organization. Approximately 600 million people live in ASEAN. This is approximately 9% of the world's population. People that live in the ASEAN region will be free to work in each other’s countries. This will allow more trained construction workers from places such as Myanmar and Cambodia to work in Thailand. The official language of ASEAN is English. </para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm674716768">.</para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm439521488">1) Why is it important to learn English? 2) Is ASEAN good for Thai people? </para>
      </section>
